who have sung in it. A History of the Rutgers University Glee Club recounts the origins of the group’s most beloved traditions, including the composition of the alma mater’s anthem “On the Banks of the Old Raritan” and the development of the annual Christmas in Carol and Song concerts. Meticulously researched, including a complete discography of the club’s recordings, this book is a must-have for all the Rutgers Glee Club’s many fans and alumni.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aGlee clubszNew JerseyzNew BrunswickxHistory. 7aMUSIC / General.2bisacsh  aGlee Club, Rutgers University, performance culture, concerts, singing, songs, college, university, singing culture, choir, music, song, student singing, Männechor Tradition, English Catch Clubs, On the Banks of the Old Raritan, Loren Bragdon, Patrick Gardner, student-run organizations, Howard D. McKinney, Raymond W. Smith, George W. Wilmot, choir gowns, songbooks.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076647940uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/9781978832268?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978832268423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978832268/original  a978-3-11-076647-9  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022b2022  a978-3-11-099375-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022